				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${H}_{kl}={H}_{kl}^{{{{{{{{\rm{HT}}}}}}}}}({H}_{kl}^{{{{{{{{\rm{ET}}}}}}}}})$$\end{document} for hole (electron) transfer), and λ is the reorganization energy for exciton or hole (electron) transfer. Large values of ΔA‡ compared to kBT are characteristic of small polaron hopping and small or vanishing values for delocalized polaronic transport. Note that the barrier height Eq. (1) is only defined for ⟨∣Hkl∣2⟩1/2<λ/2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
